<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,798,1293]" box="[151,668,834,861]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,248,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1388,194,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-19@63.[190,1397,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 10. Eudocima salaminia and Eudocima discrepans group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605520/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 10</figureCitation>
: G–I, 19: I–J, 25: G, 31: G–H, 95: N)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,798,1293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
This is a relatively large species (
<quantity box="[530,655,870,897]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="48.5" valueMax="51.0" valueMin="46.0">46–51 mm</quantity>
) with a conspicuous tornal hook and plain brownish-grey forewings, except for a few small green patches distal to the pm line. It is sexually dimorphic with two white triangular marks basal to the PM line in females. It may be confused with the smaller 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1073,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscigera">
<emphasis box="[924,1073,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">E. muscigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[1087,1211,943,969]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="37.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="36.0">36–38 mm</quantity>
) but has more elongate forewings with a more slanted outer margin. It ranges from the northeast Himalayas, W. 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1271,979,1005]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1282,1384,979,1005]" name="Thailand" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,1015,1041]" name="Vietnam" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
south to Sundaland (
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[482,662,1014,1041]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 529" refId="ref38189" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2005) The moths of Borneo (parts 15 and 16): family Noctuidae, subfamily Catocalinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 59 (1 - 4), 1 - 529." type="journal article" year="2005">Holloway 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,798,1293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
One unlabelled specimen (
<figureCitation box="[502,588,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1388,194,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-19@63.[190,1397,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 10. Eudocima salaminia and Eudocima discrepans group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605520/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
: I) differs in mtDNA, wing shape, and wing pattern. It comes out sister to the nominotypical 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[365,485,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discrepans">
<emphasis box="[365,485,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">discrepans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade with 19 COI 5’ differences between the clades (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1200,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="137.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,181,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-19@137.[151,1436,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURE 84. Strict consensus tree from a parsimony analysis of Calpinae COI 5’ mtDNA sequences (part): Eudocima clade (part)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605800/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). The forewing apex is more rounded than typical 
<emphasis box="[486,613,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[486,609,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discrepans">discrepans</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the tornus is rounded without a hook. It has a much narrower hindwing medial patch than typical 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[509,629,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discrepans">
<emphasis box="[509,629,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">discrepans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On the ventral forewing surfaces, the basal band and postmedial band are nearly concolorous pale yellow, whereas in typical 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[770,890,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discrepans">
<emphasis box="[770,890,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">discrepans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal band is orange and postmedial band is creamish-white. On the ventral hindwing anterior of vein R5 the color is pale yellow, whereas in typical 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1316,1436,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discrepans">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">discrepans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the color is creamish-white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
